<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="583" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17398</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Adjutant General</gloss> to
                                General <persName type="to">Funston</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President has directed that an armed force be sent into Mexico with the,
                            sole object of capturing Villa and preventing any further raids by his
                            band, and with scrupulous regard to sovereignty of Mexico. Secretary War
                            directs you telegraph exactly what you need in order to carry out
                            foregoing general instructions, but you will not take any overt steps
                            until receipt definite orders from War Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McCain</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>